cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.SY 

This paper focuses on the incentive mechanism for mobile crowdsensing, which involves social network effects and game theory analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also uses backward induction to analyze the optimal reward mechanism, which falls under cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper considers the impact of social networks on participation, which relates to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the revenue of the Crowdsensing Service Provider, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
